[{"id":"VH976278","type":"mcq","stimulusHtml":"<div>\n<div class=\"stimulus_reference\">\n<div class=\"standalone_image\"><img alt=\"The figure presents a diagram of a solid sphere. Points A through E, from left to right, are shown on a horizontal axis that begins at the center of the sphere. Point A is shown at the leftmost point on the axis, at a location labeled 0. Point B is shown at the location labeled 0.8 R. Point C is shown at the location labeled 1.2 R. Point D is shown at the location labeled 1.5 R, and Point E is shown at the location labeled 2.0 R. A note indicates that the figure is not drawn to scale.\" height=\"274\" src=\"https://assets.learnosity.com/organisations/537/VH976278.g01.png\" width=\"400\" /></div>\n</div>\n</div>\n\n<p class=\"stem_paragraph\">A solid sphere of radius <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"R\"><math alttext=\"R\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mstyle><mrow><mi>R</mi></mrow></mstyle></math></span></span> has charge <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"positive Q\"><math alttext=\"positive Q\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mstyle><mrow><mo>+</mo><mi>Q</mi></mrow></mstyle></math></span></span> distributed uniformly throughout its volume. The sphere and five labeled points are shown in the figure. Which of the following indicates which points would have values for the electric potential and electric field due to the sphere that are identical to the values of the electric potential and electric field if the sphere was a conducting shell of radius <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"R\"><math alttext=\"R\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mstyle><mrow><mi>R</mi></mrow></mstyle></math></span></span> and charge <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"positive Q\"><math alttext=\"positive Q\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mstyle><mrow><mo>+</mo><mi>Q</mi></mrow></mstyle></math></span></span> ?</p>\n","rubricRef":"VH976278_rubric","choicesHtml":["<p class=\"choice_paragraph\">Point <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"A\"><math alttext=\"A\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mstyle><mrow><mtext>A</mtext></mrow></mstyle></math></span></span> only</p>","<p class=\"choice_paragraph\">Point <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"B\"><math alttext=\"B\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mstyle><mrow><mtext>B</mtext></mrow></mstyle></math></span></span> only</p>","<p class=\"choice_paragraph\">Points <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"A\"><math alttext=\"A\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mstyle><mrow><mtext>A</mtext></mrow></mstyle></math></span></span> and <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"B\"><math alttext=\"B\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mstyle><mrow><mtext>B</mtext></mrow></mstyle></math></span></span> only</p>","<p class=\"choice_paragraph\">Points <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"C\"><math alttext=\"C\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mstyle><mrow><mtext>C</mtext></mrow></mstyle></math></span></span>, <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"D\"><math alttext=\"D\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mstyle><mrow><mtext>D</mtext></mrow></mstyle></math></span></span>, and <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"E\"><math alttext=\"E\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mstyle><mrow><mtext>E</mtext></mrow></mstyle></math></span></span> only</p>","<p class=\"choice_paragraph\">All the points would have the same electric potential and electric field.</p>"],"answer":3}]